        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued April 20 at 7:18PM CDT until April 20 at 8:00PM CDT by NWS Quad Cities IA IL</headline>
        <description>At 718 PM CDT, severe thunderstorms were located along a line
extending from near Bentley to near Huntsville, moving northeast at
50 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

Locations impacted include...
Pennington Point, Augusta, Western Illinois University, Adair, Bowen,
Tennessee, Colchester, Plymouth, Doddsville, Fandon, Bentley, Basco,
Industry, McDonough County 4-H Grounds, Denver, Hancock County
Fairgrounds, Colmar, Macomb, Argyle Lake State Park, and Bardolph.
</description>
        <instruction>A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 1100 PM CDT for west central
Illinois.

Remain alert for a possible tornado! Tornadoes can develop quickly
from severe thunderstorms. If you spot a tornado go at once into the
basement or small central room in a sturdy structure.

For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
sturdy building.

Torrential rainfall is occurring with these storms, and may lead to
flash flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded roadways.</instruction>
